why beauty matters is a 2009 british documentary film directed louise lockwood , written and presented by the philosopher roger scruton . scruton argues for the importance and transcendental nature of beauty . the film was a part of bbc 's project modern beauty season , which consisted of a number of programmes on the topic of beauty and modernity , broadcast during november and december 2009 . why beauty matters premiered on bbc two on 28 november 2009 .